subtropical or tropical moist lowland fo.data-term: subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest

examples.en: The loan shark sent a couple of gorillas to convince him to pay up.
Ed was fascinated to see gorillas in the wild.
Mountain gorillas are on the verge of extinction.
Researchers tracked the wild gorillas by following the piles of dung.
Her study was the first to document this type of behavior in gorillas.
Contrary to popular belief (=in spite of what many people believe), gorillas are basically shy, gentle creatures.
